# Walkthrough - Hosting Locally

I have successfully hosted the PromptLab website on your local machine.

## Changes Made

- **Environment Configuration**: Added `USE_MEMORY_DB=true` to [.env](file:///f:/PROMPTLAB/.env) to allow the server to run using an in-memory MongoDB instance. This removes the need for a local MongoDB installation for development/testing.
- **Server Startup**: Started the server using `npm run dev` with a PowerShell execution policy bypass to ensure it runs correctly on your system.

